# skill-command-refs.allow — allowlist for lint-skill-command-refs.sh
#
# The lint asserts that every slash-command a core skill presents as runnable is
# RESOLVABLE on the install it is shown to. "Resolvable" means one of:
#   1. a skill shipped in this scaffold (.claude/skills/<name>/), resolved
#      dynamically — those never need listing here; OR
#   2. a token listed below, grouped by why it is intentionally allowed.
#
# Any referenced command that is neither a shipped core skill nor listed here
# fails the lint with a file:line pointer. That is the guardrail against the
# DEV-1716 class of bug: a core skill instructing a command that does not exist
# on the user's install (the documented /run-project /execute-task dead-end).
#
# One bare token per line (no leading slash). Comments start with '#'.
# Namespaced refs (ns:cmd) and path/URL/route fragments are ignored by the
# linter itself and must NOT be listed here.

# ── Claude Code built-in slash commands ───────────────────────────────────
# Provided by the harness, not by a skill file. Add others as skills start to
# reference them (keep this minimal so a typo of a real skill name still fails).
clear
compact

# ── hq-pack-engineering commands ──────────────────────────────────────────
# The 17 engineering skills extracted from core in 15.0.0 (see
# core/docs/hq/CHANGELOG.md). They ship in the SEPARATELY-INSTALLED pack
#   hq install github:indigoai-us/hq-packages#packages/hq-pack-engineering
# and are auto-installed for upgraders but NOT for lean greenfield installs.
# CONTRACT: a core skill that instructs one of these as an actionable next step
# MUST also surface that install line so a pack-less user has a resolvable path.
architect
clean-worktree
commit-main
deep-plan
diagnose
discover
document-release
execute-task
investigate
land
land-batch
prd
quality-gate
review
run-pipeline
run-project
tdd

# ── External / maintainer commands ────────────────────────────────────────
# Not a user workflow command. The staging→hq-core promotion pipeline, surfaced
# only in maintainer-facing policy prose (learn, hq-heal). Realised by the
# personal `release-hq-core` skill + the promote-to-hq-core.yml workflow.
promote-hq-core

# ── Not commands (false positives) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Tokens that match the command shape but are an API route fragment or an
# explicit placeholder, not a runnable slash-command.
access-mode    # deploy: REST route `/access-mode` (POST /api/apps/:id/access-mode)
foo            # startwork: generic `/foo` placeholder for "any other command"
